# Design System

All typography values are stored as CSS custom properties in `app/globals.css` `@theme inline`. Reference them with `var()` — never hardcode clamp, tracking, or leading values.

## Type Scale

Custom optical scale (~Major Third body, ~Perfect Fourth headings). Defined in `--text-*` variables.

| Token | Variable | Computed | Tailwind Usage |
|-------|----------|----------|----------------|
| **Display** | `--text-display` | 44.8→140.8px | `text-[length:var(--text-display)]` |
| **Page Title** | `--text-page` | 40→72px | `text-[length:var(--text-page)]` |
| **Section Heading** | `--text-section` | 32→56px | `text-[length:var(--text-section)]` |
| **Sub Heading** | `--text-sub` | 24→40px | `text-[length:var(--text-sub)]` |
| **Service Title** | — | 24→30px | `text-2xl lg:text-3xl` |
| **Body XL** | `--text-body-xl` | 20px | `text-xl` |
| **Body Large** | `--text-body-lg` | 18px | `text-lg` |
| **Article** | `--text-article` | 17px | `text-[length:var(--text-article)]` |
| **Body** | `--text-body` | 16px | `text-base` (default) |
| **Body Small** | `--text-body-sm` | 14px | `text-sm` |
| **Caption** | `--text-caption` | 12px | `text-xs` |
| **Micro** | `--text-micro` | 10px | `text-[length:var(--text-micro)]` |

Minimum font size: **10px**. Never go below `--text-micro`.

## Font Families

### Inter (sans-serif) — `font-sans`
- Body text, UI, labels, navigation
- **Body (14–16px):** No extra tracking; Inter's defaults are tuned for this range
- **Small text (10–12px):** Positive tracking (`--tracking-sublabel` or `--tracking-label`) improves legibility
- **Uppercase:** Always add `tracking-[var(--tracking-label)]` or `tracking-[var(--tracking-sublabel)]`
- **Weight:** 400 (normal), 500 (medium), 600 (semibold). Avoid 700+ for body.
- **Min size:** 10px

### Playfair Display (serif) — `font-serif`
- Headings, display, blockquotes, large decorative numbers
- **Display (72px+):** `tracking-[var(--tracking-display)]` (-0.03em)
- **Headings (24–72px):** `tracking-tight` (-0.025em)
- **Weight:** 400 (normal) only. High stroke contrast makes bold unnecessary.
- **Line height:** 0.92–1.15 depending on size
- **Min size:** 24px (1.5rem). Below this, thin strokes become illegible.

## Leading

| Variable | Value | Usage |
|----------|-------|-------|
| `--leading-display` | 0.92 | Hero display heading only |
| `--leading-tight` | 1.05 | Page titles, footer heading |
| `--leading-heading` | 1.1 | Section headings, article h1 |
| `leading-snug` | 1.375 | Key/value snapshot items |
| `--leading-body` / `leading-relaxed` | 1.625 | Default body text |
| `--leading-longform` | 1.75 | Case study / highlight / article body |
| `leading-none` | 1 | Decorative numbers |

## Tracking

| Variable | Value | Usage |
|----------|-------|-------|
| `--tracking-display` | -0.03em | Display heading only |
| `tracking-tight` | -0.025em | All other serif headings |
| `--tracking-sublabel` | 0.12em | Sub-section labels, meta labels |
| `--tracking-label` | 0.15em | Section labels, CTA buttons |
| `tracking-wide` | 0.025em | Service meta, "View all" links |
| `tracking-widest` | 0.1em | Client marquee |

## Label Patterns

| Token | Classes |
|-------|---------|
| **Section Label** | `text-xs font-medium tracking-[var(--tracking-label)] text-accent uppercase` |
| **Sub-section Label** | `text-xs font-semibold tracking-[var(--tracking-sublabel)] text-foreground/50 uppercase` |
| **Meta Label** | `text-[length:var(--text-micro)] font-semibold tracking-[var(--tracking-sublabel)] text-accent uppercase` |
| **CTA Button** | `text-xs font-medium tracking-[var(--tracking-label)] uppercase` |

## Text Colors

| Role | Class | When |
|------|-------|------|
| Primary | `text-foreground` | Headings, author names, emphasis |
| Secondary | `text-muted-foreground` | Body paragraphs, descriptions |
| Tertiary | `text-muted-foreground/50` | Meta info, sub-labels, timestamps |
| Accent | `text-accent` | Section labels, active states, hover |
| Decorative | `text-accent/30` | Large row numbers (01, 02…) |
| On-dark | `text-primary-foreground` | Text on `bg-primary` surfaces |

Allowed opacity levels: `/30`, `/50`, `/70` only.

## Container Widths

| Token | Class | Usage |
|-------|-------|-------|
| Body text | `max-w-[60ch]` | Standard paragraphs (55-75 chars/line) |
| Article body | `max-w-[65ch]` | Long-form article reading only |
| Narrow | `max-w-[50ch]` | Intros, step descriptions |
| Title | `max-w-[20ch]` | Page titles to force wrapping |

## Section Spacing

| Token | Classes |
|-------|---------|
| Page padding | `px-8 pt-32 pb-24 lg:px-16 lg:pt-40 lg:pb-32` |
| Section gap | `mt-32` |
| Inner section | `mt-24` |
| Content gap | `gap-12 lg:gap-16` |
| Detail page | `pb-[clamp(80px,10vw,140px)] pt-28` |

## CSS Baseline (globals.css)

These are applied globally and must not be overridden:
- `font-kerning: normal` — optical pair kerning
- `font-feature-settings: 'liga' 1, 'calt' 1` — ligatures and contextual alternates
- `text-wrap: pretty` on body, p, li, blockquote
- `text-wrap: balance` on h1–h6
